The `notion-to-md` package is a powerful tool for converting Notion content into Markdown format. This guide will walk you through the process of setting up and using `notion-to-md` in your project.

## Installation

First, install the `notion-to-md` package using npm:

```bash
npm install notion-to-md
```

## Basic Usage

Here's a basic example of how to use `notion-to-md` to convert Notion content to Markdown:

```javascript
const { NotionToMarkdown } = require("notion-to-md");

const n2m = new NotionToMarkdown({ notionClient: yourNotionClient });

const markdown = await n2m.pageToMarkdown("your-page-id");
console.log(markdown);
```

## Advanced Configuration

You can customize the conversion process with various options:

```javascript
const n2m = new NotionToMarkdown({
  notionClient: yourNotionClient,
  config: {
    separateChildPage: true,
    convertImage: true,
    // other options...
  }
});
```

## Converting Blocks

To convert specific Notion blocks to Markdown:

```javascript
const markdownBlocks = await n2m.blocksToMarkdown(blocks);
```

## Handling Tables

For converting Notion tables to Markdown:

```javascript
const tableMarkdown = await n2m.tableBlockToMarkdown(tableBlock);
```

## Error Handling

Always include error handling in your implementation:

```javascript
try {
  const markdown = await n2m.pageToMarkdown("your-page-id");
  console.log(markdown);
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Conversion failed:", error);
}
```

## Example Output

The output will be a Markdown string with the content from your Notion page, including all formatting, images, and other elements.

